==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mechanico-chemical
<hw>Me*chan`i*co-chem"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Pertaining to, connected with, or dependent upon, both mechanics
and chemistry; -- said especially of those sciences which treat of such
phenomena as seem to depend on the laws both of mechanics and chemistry,
as electricity and magnetism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mechanics</ent>⟦br⟧
